    "created_at": "2023-05-16T02:32:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-05-16T02:36:25Z",
    "body": "I have a weird error related to UTF8 encoding stuffs when using mambaforge with starship on windows (both bash and power shell).\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nreturn codecs.charmap_encode(input,self.errors,encoding_table)[0]\r\n    UnicodeEncodeError: 'charmap' codec can't encode character '\\u276f' in position 130: character maps to <undefined>\r\n \r\n```\r\n\r\nChanging condarc to include `changeps1: False` also fixes the problem to me.\r\n\r\nI guess the reason this weird problem happens is that starship uses some special UTF8 characters for the shell prompt, and the code of mambaforge that handles add env name to the shell prompt is not robust enough to handle those special characters.",
